urlText: L2 and L3 partial line closures during Vivid Sydney on Fridays and weekends
content:
During Vivid Sydney from Friday 24 May to Saturday 15 June, L2 Randwick Line and L3 Kingsford Line light rail services will be affected on Friday nights and weekends.
  • On Fridays from 6pm to 1am and on weekends (Saturdays, Sundays and public holiday Mon 10 June) from 5pm to 1am, L2 and L3 light rail services will not run between Town Hall and Circular Quay due to road closures and for pedestrian safety.
  • Light rail services will continue to run between Town Hall and Randwick or Juniors Kingsford during these times.
  • If you’re travelling to Circular Quay, continue on foot from Town Hall or change for trains.
  • Note on Saturdays and on Sunday 9 June from 6pm to 11pm, Sydney Trains services will not drop off passengers at Circular Quay Station – use Wynyard, Martin Place or St James stations instead.
  • L1 Dulwich Hill Line light rail services will run as per normal during Vivid Sydney from 5am to 1am daily.
  • Allow extra travel time as services will be very busy, and plan ahead using the Trip Planner to see if your travel is affected.
 Visit the Vivid Sydney event page for more details on transport services during the event.

urlText: Buses replace trains between Bomaderry and Wollongong
content:
Sunday 30 June
  • From 2.30am to 9.50am, buses replace trains between Bomaderry and Wollongong.
  • You may need to change buses to continue your journey.
  • Trains run between Port Kembla, Wollongong and Bondi Junction, some to a changed timetable.
  • The 02:39 Kiama to Bondi Junction service will run up to 14 minutes earlier than the normal timetable from Kiama to Coniston, then run to the normal timetable from Wollongong to Bondi Junction.

  • Replacement buses may be impacted by driver shortages. We are doing all we can to minimise the impact to your journey and provide a safe service, however cancellations or delays may occur.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date real time information. You can also subscribe to planned trackwork alerts.
Bus routes
1SC Bomaderry, then all stations to Kiama and return
2SC Kiama, then Wollongong and return
3SC Dapto, then all stations to Wollongong (one direction only)
5SC Kiama, then Bombo, Minnamurra, Shellharbour Junction, Oak Flats and return (bypassing Bombo in the Oak Flats direction)

urlText: Ferries will be busy during Vivid Sydney
content:
Ferry customers are advised to expect delays and long queues for ferries to and from the city during Vivid Sydney from Friday 24 May to Saturday 15 June. Services will be busy and are expected to reach capacity from mid-afternoon, particularly on weekends. Some additional ferries will run on weeknights and weekends during the event.
 
Vivid Sydney attendees planning to catch a ferry to precincts around Circular Quay, Barangaroo or Pyrmont should plan ahead and have a back-up transport option in mind, from most wharves you can catch buses to the city or to nearby train stations to continue your trip.
 
Ferries in the harbour will also be affected by Vivid Sydney Drone Shows taking place on the evenings of Saturday 8, Sunday 9 and Saturday 15 June. Ferries will not run to or from Circular Quay from 9pm to 9.30pm on these dates. F1 Manly ferries will drop off and pick up from Barangaroo wharf instead, other ferry routes will run to an altered timetable arriving and departing Circular Quay before 9pm and after 9.30pm.
 
Visit the Vivid Sydney event page for more details on transport services during the event.

content:

  • Captain Cook Cruises operates a commuter ferry service during peak travel times from Greenwich Wharf Bay Street. Please check their website for more information.
  • Allow extra travel time, listen to announcements and check information displays for service updates.
  • For more information on the Greenwich Point Wharf Upgrade please visit the Greenwich Point Wharf Upgrade page.

urlText: L1, L2 and L3 light rail services may be temporarily held at stops or partially closed due to a Police Operation
content:
On Sunday 16 June, L1 Dulwich Hill Line, L2 Randwick Line and L3 Kingsford Line light rail services may be impacted between 2pm and 2.30pm approximately due to road closures around Central Station for a planned Police Operation protest march:
  • L1 services may be temporarily held at stops, or temporarily partially closed between Central Grand Concourse and Convention, and/or
  • L2 and L3 services may be temporarily held at stops, or temporarily partially closed between Circular Quay or Central Chalmers Street.
    Impact to services and timings may change at the direction of NSW Police.
 Please check information screens at stops, listen to announcements and follow the direction of staff or Police on site, as necessary.
 
Allow extra travel time and use the Trip Planner for alternative transport options.
